data.text:
Gilbert Belnap - A black and white photo of a man with a beard

Photo of Gilbert Belnap, a Mormon pioneer, LDS Church leader, and an early colonizer of Ogden, Utah, Fort Lemhi, Idaho and Hooper, Utah.

Shadrach roundy - An old black and white photo of a man in a tuxedo

Photo of Shadrach Roundy, an early Latter Day Saint who was the second oldest member of Brigham Young's Company, which arrived in the Salt Lake Valley in 1847, and was one of the advance party which arrived in ... More

Eldred G. Smith - A black and white photo of a man in a suit

Photo of Eldred Gee Smith, ca 1952, the patriarch emeritus to The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) and previously a Patriarch to the between 1947 and 1979.

Henry D. Taylor - A black and white photo of a man in a suit and tie

Photo of Henry D. Taylor, a general authority in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. Tayolor was a member of the First Quorum of the Seventy and an Assistant to the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles.

William R. Smith (Mormon)

Photo of William R. Smith a Utah territorial politician and a leader of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) in Utah Territory.

Samuel Claridge - A black and white photo of a man with a beard

Photo of Samuel Claridge a prominent early settler of the Muddy River Valley in Nevada and also Thatcher, Arizona.

Hiram B. Clawson - A black and white photo of a man with a mustache

Photo of Hiram B. Clawson, a Latter-day Saint businessman and Church leader in the 19th and early 20th centuries.

Horton D. Haight - A black and white photo of a man with a mustache

A Photo of Horton D. Haight was a Mormon pioneer and grandfather of David B. Haight (an apostle in the LDS Church.The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints).

Joseph L. Heywood - A black and white photo of a man with a long beard

Photo of Joseph L. Heywood, a local leader of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) in the 19th century, and the founder of Nephi, Utah.

L. John Nuttall - A black and white photo of a man with a long beard

Photo of L. John Nuttall, a private secretary for John Taylor, and Wilford Woodruff and was a member of the Council of Fifty who kept a detailed journal of the early history of The Church of Jesus Christ of La ... More

Daniel Spencer (Mormon)

Photo of Daniel Spencer, the last mayor of Nauvoo, Illinois prior to the revocation of its first charter in 1846.

David King Udall - A black and white photo of a man with a beard

Photo of David King Udall, a representative to the Arizona Territorial Legislature and the founder of the Udall political family.
